    <content type="html">&lt;p&gt;
	I love button walls but now and then, when saving a site‚Äôs button, I find it‚Äôs 88x33 instead of 88x31 and using only the &lt;em&gt;width&lt;/em&gt; and &lt;em&gt;height&lt;/em&gt; attributes ends up breaking my layout. It seems that browsers follow the height attribute and reduce the width accordingly. I came up with a solution that worked for me (adding a little &lt;em&gt;style&lt;/em&gt;) - it may not be the ‚Äôbest practice‚Äô but I decided to share just in case others find it useful: 
